11 An Act relating to the Department of Human Services;
making appropriations; stating purposes; providing an
12 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Department of
17 Human Services, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
18 Statewide Recovery Fund (497) of the State Treasury, the sum of
19 Three Million Dollars ($3,000,000.00) or so much thereof as may be
20 necessary to provide funding to the Boys and Girls Clubs in
21 Oklahoma. Such funds shall be utilized in a manner consistent with
22 the recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic
23 Relief Funding on April 15, 2026.
24
Req. No. 3954 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. There is hereby appropriated to the Department of
2 Human Services, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
3 Statewide Recovery Fund (497) of the State Treasury, the sum of Six
4 Hundred Thousand Dollars ($600,000.00) or so much thereof as may be
5 necessary to provide funding to the Young Women’s Christian
6 Association (YWCA). Such funds shall be utilized in a manner
7 consistent with the recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee
8 on Pandemic Relief Funding on April 15, 2026.
9 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
10 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
11 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
12 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
13 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
